properties.areaDesc: Orange County Coastal; San Diego County Coastal Areas
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 23 at 9:43PM PST until January 26 at 6:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ALONG THE COAST THIS WEEKEND...

A strong west swell from 285 degrees will bring areas of high
surf along the beaches. Highest surf will be in southern San
Diego County and northern Orange County where 6 to 8 foot surf,
locally higher, will be likely Saturday. The surf will lower by
about one foot on Sunday. The period will be high, 15 to
18 seconds. The high surf will be accompanied by dangerous rip
currents. The surf should lower late Sunday and Monday.

* Waves and Surf...6 to 8 feet, locally higher, in southern San
Diego County and northern Orange County. Elsewhere, 4 to 6
feet.

* Timing...Late Friday night through Sunday, with highest surf
Saturday.

* Tides...La Jolla high tide Saturday of 5.8 feet at 852 AM,
followed by a low tide of -0.9 feet at 359 PM.

* Impacts...Dangerous swimming conditions and a high risk of rip
currents. Local beach erosion possible. Always swim near a
lifeguard!
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area...producing localized beach erosion and
dangerous swimming conditions.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM FRIDAY TO 6 PM PST SUNDAY
